<paragraph id="680036C1516D7243189EF89ED1B4F853" blockId="14.[151,793,1862,1922]" box="[151,440,1897,1922]" pageId="14" pageNumber="51">
(Pls 1E, 3–5E, 7E; 
<figureCitation id="F0842A44516D72431964F89ED1BCF853" box="[365,432,1897,1922]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1816,1838]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,404,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[159,1423,404,1791]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Lordiphosa mikioides sp. nov. (A−L: holotype 06060; N−O: paratype 06061). A, sex-combs on left foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstylus and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H̅J, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); K, L, apical shape of paramere(s) and sensillum (ventral and ventrolateral view, respectively; red arrow indicates sensillum); M, N, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); O, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439535/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="51">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="20A5654A516D7242189EF846D4CEFEB6" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="14" pageNumber="51" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="680036C1516D7242189EF846D4CEFEB6" blockId="14.[151,1436,1969,2030]" lastBlockId="15.[151,1436,151,357]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="14" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD3516D7243189EF846D11DF818" bold="true" box="[151,273,1969,1994]" pageId="14" pageNumber="51">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Arista almost bare, though sometimes with 1 or 2 dorsal, minute branches (Pl. 4E). First and 2nd tarsomeres of male foreleg dorsodistally extended, with sex-combs: 1 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF4D42516D72431B95F821D42BF83F" box="[924,1063,2006,2030]" pageId="14" pageNumber="51" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="tarsomere">st tarsomere</taxonomicName>
with a longitudinal row of ca. 29 black, apically blunt teeth along entire length and a distal cluster of ca. 10 black, apically sharp teeth; 2nd tarsomere with a distal cluster of ca. 8 black, apically sharp teeth (
<figureCitation id="F0842A44516C72421B97FF4BD419FF06" box="[926,1045,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1816,1838]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,404,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[159,1423,404,1791]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Lordiphosa mikioides sp. nov. (A−L: holotype 06060; N−O: paratype 06061). A, sex-combs on left foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstylus and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H̅J, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); K, L, apical shape of paramere(s) and sensillum (ventral and ventrolateral view, respectively; red arrow indicates sensillum); M, N, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); O, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439535/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Fig. 7A,B</figureCitation>
). Cercus ventrally tapered, with a fringe of 11 spines on apicoventral margin (
<figureCitation id="F0842A44516C72421A93FF28D32BFF2A" box="[666,807,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1816,1838]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,404,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[159,1423,404,1791]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Lordiphosa mikioides sp. nov. (A−L: holotype 06060; N−O: paratype 06061). A, sex-combs on left foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstylus and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H̅J, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); K, L, apical shape of paramere(s) and sensillum (ventral and ventrolateral view, respectively; red arrow indicates sensillum); M, N, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); O, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439535/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Fig. 7C,D,F</figureCitation>
). Paramere flat, somewhat blade-shaped, only slightly curved ventrad, apically sharp and broader, subapically with 1 acute, dorsal, somewhat membranous process bearing 1 sensillum at apex (
<figureCitation id="F0842A44516C724219D7FED0D255FE92" box="[478,601,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1816,1838]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,404,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[159,1423,404,1791]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Lordiphosa mikioides sp. nov. (A−L: holotype 06060; N−O: paratype 06061). A, sex-combs on left foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstylus and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H̅J, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); K, L, apical shape of paramere(s) and sensillum (ventral and ventrolateral view, respectively; red arrow indicates sensillum); M, N, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); O, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439535/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Fig. 7H–L</figureCitation>
). Gonopods shorter than aedeagus, dorsoapically with long, acute process (
<figureCitation id="F0842A44516C72421896FEBBD0FCFEB6" box="[159,240,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1816,1838]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,404,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[159,1423,404,1791]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Lordiphosa mikioides sp. nov. (A−L: holotype 06060; N−O: paratype 06061). A, sex-combs on left foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstylus and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H̅J, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); K, L, apical shape of paramere(s) and sensillum (ventral and ventrolateral view, respectively; red arrow indicates sensillum); M, N, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); O, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439535/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Fig. 7J</figureCitation>
). Spermathecal capsule not wrinkled horizontally, without apical indentation (
<figureCitation id="F0842A44516C72421C52FEBBD4B9FEB6" box="[1115,1205,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1816,1838]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,404,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[159,1423,404,1791]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Lordiphosa mikioides sp. nov. (A−L: holotype 06060; N−O: paratype 06061). A, sex-combs on left foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstylus and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H̅J, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); K, L, apical shape of paramere(s) and sensillum (ventral and ventrolateral view, respectively; red arrow indicates sensillum); M, N, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); O, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439535/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Fig. 7O</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="3CC06649516C7242189EF8EFD48EF806" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439535/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" startId="15.[151,250,1816,1838]" targetBox="[159,1423,404,1791]" targetPageId="15">
