<subSubSection id="20A5654A5173725D18CEFF60D237FB8A" pageId="16" pageNumber="53" type="description">
<paragraph id="680036C15173725D18CEFF60D500FEB6" blockId="16.[151,1437,151,1400]" pageId="16" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD35173725D18CEFF60D15DFF62" bold="true" box="[199,337,151,176]" pageId="16" pageNumber="53">Description</emphasis>
(
<specimenCount id="7EB9FD485173725D196DFF6FD177FF62" box="[356,379,152,176]" pageId="16" pageNumber="53" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
, 
<specimenCount id="7EB9FD485173725D1981FF6FD190FF62" box="[392,412,152,176]" pageId="16" pageNumber="53" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
). Head (Pls 1E, 3–5E, 7E): Frontal vitta, fronto-orbital plate, ocellar triangle, face, facial carina, and gena yellowish brown; fronto-orbital plate somewhat paler than frontal vitta. Occiput dorsally yellowish brown, ventrally dark brown. Postgena yellowish brown, dark brown along margin of occiput. Antennal pedicel yellowish brown; 1 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF4D425173725D19C3FEF3D27BFECF" box="[458,631,260,285]" pageId="16" pageNumber="53" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="flagellomere">st flagellomere</taxonomicName>
pale grayish yellow. Supracervical setulae 19¯21 per side; postocular setae 17–18 per side. Palpus pale yellowish brown. Clypeus yellowish brown. Cibarium with 18–23 medial and 17–19 posterior sensilla per side. Prementum with 5 (1 proximal, 2 lateral, and 2 distal) pairs of setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="680036C15173725D18CEFE98D2F5FE7F" blockId="16.[151,1437,151,1400]" pageId="16" pageNumber="53">Thorax (Pl. 1E) yellowish brown. Postpronotal lobe pale yellow. Acrostichal setulae in 6 regular rows. Mid katepisternal seta distinctly longer than those below it.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="680036C15173725D18CEFE4FD597FE1D" blockId="16.[151,1437,151,1400]" box="[199,1435,439,464]" pageId="16" pageNumber="53">
Legs (Pl. 1E, 
<figureCitation id="F0842A445173725D1969FE40D1DFFE02" box="[352,467,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1816,1838]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,404,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[159,1423,404,1791]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Lordiphosa mikioides sp. nov. (A−L: holotype 06060; N−O: paratype 06061). A, sex-combs on left foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstylus and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H̅J, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); K, L, apical shape of paramere(s) and sensillum (ventral and ventrolateral view, respectively; red arrow indicates sensillum); M, N, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); O, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439535/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="53">Fig. 7A,B</figureCitation>
): Fore- and midleg 1 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF4D425173725D1AB0FE4FD35CFE1D" box="[697,848,440,464]" pageId="16" pageNumber="53" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="tarsomeres">st tarsomeres</taxonomicName>
longer than total length of 4 succeeding tarsomeres.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="680036C15173725D18CEFE2BD371FE27" blockId="16.[151,1437,151,1400]" box="[199,893,476,501]" pageId="16" pageNumber="53">Abdomen (Pl. 1E): Tergites entirely yellow, somewhat glossy.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="680036C15173725D18CEFE08D54DFD1F" blockId="16.[151,1437,151,1400]" pageId="16" pageNumber="53">
Male terminalia (
<figureCitation id="F0842A445173725D1983FE08D208FDCA" box="[394,516,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1816,1838]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,404,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[159,1423,404,1791]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Lordiphosa mikioides sp. nov. (A−L: holotype 06060; N−O: paratype 06061). A, sex-combs on left foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstylus and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H̅J, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); K, L, apical shape of paramere(s) and sensillum (ventral and ventrolateral view, respectively; red arrow indicates sensillum); M, N, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); O, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439535/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="53">Fig. 7C–L</figureCitation>
): Epandrium dorsally broadened, only caudomedially pubescent, with ca. 15 long setae per side; ventral lobe not elongated, triangular in lateral view. Cercus entirely pubescent, setigerous (but number of setae uncountable due to bad conditions of dissected organs long preserved in glycerin). Surstylus with a row of ca. 15 prensisetae on caudal margin and ca. 51 setae on ventral portion of inner surface. Tenth sternite broken. Hypandrial caudolateral lobes unpubescent. Aedeagus apically slightly bent ventrad, medially to basally membranous, sheathed with gonopods; apodeme apically broadened in lateral view, shorter than aedeagus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="680036C15173725D18CEFD20D339FC8F" blockId="16.[151,1437,151,1400]" pageId="16" pageNumber="53">
Female terminalia (
<figureCitation id="F0842A445173725D19A8FD20D228FD22" box="[417,548,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1816,1838]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,404,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[159,1423,404,1791]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Lordiphosa mikioides sp. nov. (A−L: holotype 06060; N−O: paratype 06061). A, sex-combs on left foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstylus and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H̅J, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); K, L, apical shape of paramere(s) and sensillum (ventral and ventrolateral view, respectively; red arrow indicates sensillum); M, N, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); O, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439535/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="53">Fig. 7M–O</figureCitation>
): Tergite VIII yellow, pubescent except for anteromedial margin, caudodorsally swollen in lateral view. Epiproct and hypoproct yellow. Oviscapt valve apically triangular in lateral view, with ca. 14 marginal and ca. 85 minute, lateral ovisensilla. Spermathecal capsule hemispherical, nearly as broad as long; introvert about 1/2 height of capsule, horizontally wrinkled.
</paragraph>
